This paper deals with dimensionality reduction, a topic that is commonly studied in machine learning (cs.LG) and data science (cs.DS). The paper also introduces a new problem related to fairness in dimensionality reduction, which is a topic of interest in artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and social impact (cs.SI). The paper also involves the use of semi-definite programming (SDP), which is a topic in information theory (cs.IT). Therefore, the most likely sub-categories are cs.LG, cs.DS, cs.IT, cs.AI, and cs.SI.
